Feature guidance

## User issue
The user does not understand a feature or is unsure about what step to take.

## Possible causes
- The feature is not explained clearly
- The interface is confusing
- There is not enough visual guidance
- The user is unfamiliar with the workflow

## Troubleshooting steps
1. Identify which part is unclear for the user.
2. Giving a clear explanation in simple language.
3. Breaking the process into small steps.
3. Suggest the issue could be improved by the interface or documentation changes.
4. Collect similar feedback to identify usability patterns.

## User-friendly response
Here is how this feature works. First, click on the relevant link, then you are able to access the surface for step1. Then do step one. You will be able to see another field, then do step 2. Finally, you can do step 3 at the bottom of the page. Please let me know if anything is unclear, and I can help further.

## Internal note
The issue may be related to user-side unfamiliarity. Possibly unclear frontend design, or unclear documentation.
